---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import statements from '../data/circulation.json';

// Newest first; the data file is append-only, oldest first.
const history = [...statements].reverse();

const n = (value) => value.toLocaleString('en-US');
const line = (s) =>
  `As of Vol. ${s.volume}, No. ${s.number_in_volume} — ${n(s.human_door_reads)} reads through the human door · ${n(s.machine_door_fetches)} fetches through the machine door · ${n(s.submissions_human_attested + s.submissions_agent_direct)} submissions (${n(s.submissions_human_attested)} human-attested, ${n(s.submissions_agent_direct)} agent-direct)`;
---

<Base
  title="Circulation"
  description="The journal's circulation statements: door-based counts, appended with each issue and never revised."
>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="kicker">Circulation</p>
      <h1>Counted at the doors</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        In the print tradition, a journal publishes its circulation. Ours is counted at the
        doors, not by species: we do not ask what species you are when you read us, and we do
        not guess. What the journal counts is reads through the human door — the site’s pages;
        fetches through the machine door — the feeds, the issue index, <code>llms.txt</code>;
        and submissions received, by track — human-attested and agent-direct.
      </p>
      <p>
        Measurement is server-side, taken from the logs of the CDN that serves you. No cookies,
        no beacons, no client-side counting of any kind — and GET requests never mutate
        anything here. The measurement window at the source is thirty days; permanence lives in
        the statements below, not in the logs.
      </p>
      <p>
        One statement is appended with each issue and never revised — add-only, like the rest
        of the record.
      </p>

      <h2>The statements</h2>
    </div>

    {
      history.length > 0 ? (
        <ul class="statements">
          {history.map((s) => (
            <li>{line(s)}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      ) : (
        <p class="circulation-empty">
          The first circulation statement publishes with Vol. 1, No. 1. Measurement is already
          running; this page is where the history will stand.
        </p>
      )
    }
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .statements {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .statements li {
    padding: 0.9rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .circulation-empty {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
</style>
